@startuml child-resource-ownership-async
' The one link that cannot be an ownerRef: async response ConfigMaps live in another namespace.
' Source of truth: docs/src/runtime/child-resources.md
!include _style.puml

skinparam nodesep 18
skinparam ranksep 40
skinparam rectangle {
  roundCorner 4
}

rectangle "namespace: **team-support**" as nsuser #line:4A148C;line.dashed;text:2a0a4a {
  rectangle "**AgentChannel**\nsupport-slack\nfinalizer: kaalm.io/channel-finalizer" as chan #back:E6E6FA;line:4A148C;line.bold;text:2a0a4a
}

rectangle "namespace: **kaalm-system**" as nssys #line:1B5E20;line.dashed;text:0b3d0b {
  rectangle "**ConfigMap** kaalm-async-{requestId}\nlabels:\n  kaalm.io/channel-namespace: team-support\n  kaalm.io/channel-name: support-slack\nannotation: kaalm.io/expires-at (1h)" as cm #back:FFD580;line:7a3f00;line.bold;text:3a1f00
}

chan -[#B71C1C,dashed]-> cm : **linked by labels, not ownerRef**\nswept explicitly by the\nchannel finalizer

note right of cm
  **Why no ownerRef.** A cross-namespace ownerReference
  is invalid. The GC resolves the owner in the //dependent's//
  namespace, finds nothing, and deletes the ConfigMap
  **immediately**, emitting OwnerRefInvalidNamespace.

  So nothing collects these. Cleanup is two explicit paths:
  the reconciler prunes expired entries by label selector on
  every pass, and the channel finalizer sweeps the whole
  label-matched set after the gateway confirms disconnect.
end note

legend bottom
  **Red dashed** = label linkage with no owner: invisible to cascade GC,
  and therefore the only child that needs an explicit finalizer sweep.
endlegend
@enduml
